description: {"blocks":[{"key":"b0f2q","text":"Borrelia burgdorferi (Bb), the causative agent of Lyme disease, must adapt to vastly different environments as the bacterium cycles between the tick vector and a vertebrate host. During a bloodmeal, Bb migrates from the tick midgut to the salivary glands and changes its gene expression, priming Bb for vertebrate infection. These tick-specific events are dependent on key transcriptional regulators; however, the full range of transcriptional changes that occur inside of the tick over the course of several days during transmission are technically difficult to capture. We developed an experimental approach to enrich Bb cells from Ixodes ticks during a transmitting bloodmeal to longitudinally define their global transcriptomic landscape. We identified 192 genes that change expression at least twofold over the course of the tick bloodmeal, which were predominantly located on plasmids of the Bb genome. The majority of upregulated genes encode proteins found at the cell envelope or proteins of unknown function, including 45 upregulated outer surface lipoproteins embedded in the unusual protein-rich coat of Bb. The ex vivo Bb transcriptomes provide an important roadmap for investigating key determinants of Bb priming and transmission during the tick stage of its unique transmission cycle.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":20},{"style":"italic","offset":22,"length":2},{"style":"italic","offset":199,"length":2},{"style":"italic","offset":296,"length":2},{"style":"italic","offset":620,"length":2},{"style":"italic","offset":634,"length":7},{"style":"italic","offset":898,"length":3},{"style":"italic","offset":1116,"length":2},{"style":"italic","offset":1124,"length":11},{"style":"italic","offset":1217,"length":3}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
materials_text: {"blocks":[{"key":"3llvc","text":"Dounce grinder (Kimble: 885303-0002) with 2 pestles","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ou0c","text":"Phosphate Buffered Saline (PBS) (3 mL/sample)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1uduk","text":"anti-Bb antibody (Invitrogen: PA1-73004; RRID: AB_1016668) (2 μL/sample)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dct5n","text":"Dynabeads Protein G (Invitrogen 10003D) (50 μL/sample)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3dkt0","text":"Magnet for 1.5 mL tubes (such as MagJET Separation Rack, 12 x 1.5 mL tube, Thermo Scientific MR02)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5cls3","text":"Trizol (Invitrogen 15596018) (1.5 ml/sample)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dm7k8","text":"RNase-free non-stick 1.5 ml tubes (such as Invitrogen AM12450)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4goq9","text":"Add ticks and 500 μL of PBS to the dounce grinder and homogenize using pestle A (large clearance pestle) 10 times up and down.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b5fem","text":"Collect ticks for homogenization. We recommend using between 6-14 nymphal ticks depending on day of feeding. Ticks can be washed with water or surface sterilized with 1% bleach before beginning.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dudg8","text":"Remove pestle A and homogenize with pestle B (small clearance pestle) 5 times up and down.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"egm7t","text":"Move homogenate to a 1.5 mL tube and increase the volume to 1 mL with PBS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1u13m","text":"For an input sample: take out 50 μL of the sample and add 500 μL of Trizol. {"blocks":[{"key":"4fo0o","text":"Place the tube on the magnet and remove the supernatant (the depleted fraction) into a new tube. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"es5ag","text":"Place the tube on the magnet, remove the second PBS wash and resuspend the beads in 500 μL Trizol.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
